The paper proposes a trainable multiplication layer for neural networks that can be used to extract auto-correlation and co-occurrence from input images and feature maps. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the training of the TML using backpropagation with constraints, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also mentions the use of the TML for classification, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates the applicability of the TML using public datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
